id: pmc-2lzr
title: Fix large tracker generation buffer limit
description: pm-changelog fails on large pm list-all --json output because readPmItems uses spawnSync with Node's default maxBuffer. Increase the package-owned reader buffer and cover the regression so the pm extension command works in large real trackers.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: bug,changelog,extension,release
created_at: "2026-05-23T20:36:00.133Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-24T12:09:13.715Z"
author: codex-pm-changelog
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: "- readPmItems handles pm list-all --json output larger than Node's default spawnSync buffer.\\n- A regression test covers JSON output above 1 MiB.\\n- The shipped dist artifacts are rebuilt from TypeScript source.\\n- npm run release:check passes after changelog regeneration."
reviewer: steve
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-05-release
release: v2026.05.23-2
severity: high
resolution: "Raised readPmItems default maxBuffer to 64 MiB with an explicit maxBuffer override, rebuilt shipped dist artifacts, and added regression coverage for >1 MiB pm JSON."
expected_result: pm changelog generate and readPmItems handle large pm list-all --json output from real trackers.
actual_result: "npm test passes including large JSON regression; npm run release:check passes after generated changelog is current."
affected_version: 2026.5.23-1
fixed_version: 2026.5.23-2
component: generator
